	<hr WIDTH="100%">
	<h2>Introduction:</h2>
	This lab exercises the ability to:
	<ul>
	    <li>construct and test compound hardware Boolean circuits, from circuit diagrams, using breadboard kits.
	</ul>
	<h2>Lab Assignment:</h2>

	Form into pairs (in the hardware lab), then complete and test the following task:
	    <ul> 
		<li>construct a <b>four-bit</b>
		<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adder_(electronics)">adder</a>
		using four
		<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adder_(electronics)#Full_adder">full adders</a>
		based on the following logic design,<br>
<!--
		<a href="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/aa/Full_Adder.svg">logic design</a>
-->
		<img src="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs200/labs/XOR_Full_Adder.svg" alt="Full adder design from OR, AND, &amp; XOR logic" /><br>
<!--
		<img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/aa/Full_Adder.svg" alt="Full adder design from OR, AND, &amp; XOR logic" /><br>
		<img src="XOR_Full_Adder.svg" alt="Full adder design from OR, AND, &amp; XOR logic" /><br>
-->
		<img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/aa/Full_Adder.svg" alt="Full adder design from OR, AND, &amp; XOR logic" /><br>
		which configures a full-adder from an <b>OR</b> gate, two <b>AND</b> gates and two
		<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xor">XOR</a> (exclusive OR)
		gates.
		<hr>
		<img src="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs200/labs/7486diagram.gif" alt="7486 XOR chip diagram" /><br>
		<ul> 
		    <li> <a href="http://sensorsweep.tripod.com/7486.html">7486 - Quad 2-Input Exclusive-OR (XOR) gate diagram</a> 
		</ul> 
		</li> 
		<hr>
		<li>Draw wires to connect the the chips to implement the 4-bit adder design on
		    <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs200/labs/XOR_full_adder_chips.pdf">this template</a>.
	    </ul>

	Demonstrate your correctly operating circuit to the instructor.
